<br>
Warriors need SOMETHING. Honestly, I don't think better tanking is the only answer.<br>
<br>
1. It doesn't stack.<br>
<br>
2. Yeah, to be honest, we shouldn't be REQUIRED for a raid. Niether should a shammy, mage, ench, or cleric, really.<br>
<br>
3. Lets say Cheal was changed to heal 100k hp every cast, and cost 1 mana, and we were given 100k hp. Yeah, you now only need one cleric if you have a warrior. And still, cheal chain on an SK with Modrod2 support would let the wizard nuke harder and faster, meaning a faster kill.<br>
<br>
Better taunt, yeah, that helps. Better damage, wonderfull, that stacks. Silly gimmicks like Warcry (or whatever the anti fear AA ability is) being changed to last 4 miniutes, be on a 10 min reuse time, and add 100atk and 10 mana/hp regen and 100 ac or something to the whole group and not take a buff slot... That would be great.<br>
<br>
The perfect fix, to me, the fix I want- Nerf Modrod2. Remove it from game. Mages would object because it makes them much less wanted on raids. Fine, give them something else to make em wanted. I read Magecompendium, I play a rodwhore in addition to my warrior, few if any of them LIKE rodwhoring. Most mages would cheer, provided it was replaced with a similiarly wanted spell/skill. But it won't happen. Ssra would be impossible with that, for example. Warriors would be best tank if mana was a concern, SK or Pally if got overkill and just wanna speed up the kill a bit, switching MA's when defensive runs out would become a tactic that is actually used, etc. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=17853>Cyrz Bloodscale</a>
Help your fellow brethern, and help shall come to ye when you need it</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukepletp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keple tp</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/4/02 3:00:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1190.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Yeah, SK's won't tank anything decent.. Read on</span><hr size=1> Remove mod rod 2 from mages and allow them to summon focus items that have a number of charges (for example 5-6 casts but with much better effects that what they have right now). That would keep them busy during fight while providing a very valuable role on raids and being stackable. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubburlydorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BBurlydorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/5/02 4:28:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1190.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Yeah, SK's won't tank anything decent.. Read on</span><hr size=1> Warriors have been seriously reverse-nerfed at all levels over the last 6 months or so. The comments about Modrod2 and SK taunt are a certain indicator.<br>
<br>
Already the way to take an easy mob like Dain is to make a bunch of Modrods, start CH rotation on a well-equipped SK that is standing in a corner, have him cast a high-aggro spell on Dain, with the Hate list manipulating spells maintain aggro on him while high DPS melees get Dain to half. Finish Dain off with Wizard DD. The whole trick with mobile mobs is to get them locked on a MT instead of running around killing people - Sk's can do this.<br>
<br>
Sure, you can have a couple of Warriors in there with Defensive and AE Taunt, but they will not be able to hold aggro as well as the SK. At best they are Rampage Tanks.<br>
<br>
If you are putting a CT or Velks group together do you really prefer a Warior to a Knight? I think not.<br>
<br>
For 90% of the raid mobs in the game how many EB weilding Warriors are NEEDED in your guild? 5? 3? Not too many is it?<br>
<br>
Sure, some guilds will be forced to use older less-efficient tactics because they've invested in Warriors and not SK's, Monks, and Wizards.<br>
<br>
The point is not if Warriors should be required. They once were and now they clearly aren't. That my friends is a nerf. Needed??-heck in many cases we're not even wanted.<br>
<br>
BB<br>
Battleblade Burlydorf<br>
60 Warrior<br>
Noctus Erus<br>
